1 Sec. 5. 29-A MRSA §1304, sub-§1-C is enacted to read:
2 1-C. Learner's permit; exception to driver education for issuance to adults. A
3 person who is at least 18 years of age may apply for a learner's permit for the purposes of
4 learning how to drive if:
5 A. The person has successfully passed all parts of an examination other than the driving
6 test; or
7 B. The person has successfully completed a driver education course that includes only
8 classroom instruction through an adult education program and has been issued a
9 completion certificate under section 1351, subsection 3.
10 Notwithstanding paragraph B, a driver education course that includes only classroom
11 instruction through an adult education program may issue a learner's permit pursuant to
12 subsection 1-A, paragraph D if the person being issued the learner's permit is at least 18
13 years of age and has successfully completed the course.
14 Sec. 6. 29-A MRSA §1351, sub-§2, as amended by PL 1997, c. 393, Pt. A, §35
15 and affected by §37 and amended by PL 2003, c. 545, §5, is further amended to read:
16 2. Approved course. An approved driver education course is a course given by a:
17 A. Public A public secondary school;
18 B. Private A private secondary school approved for attendance purposes by the
19 Commissioner of Education;
20 C. Career A career and technical education center or a career and technical education
21 region; or
22 C-1. An adult education program; or
23 D. Person A person licensed by the Secretary of State.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This bill creates an exception to the law that a learner's permit applicant must complete
2266 a course in driver education prior to being issued a learner's permit. The bill allows a person
2277 who is 15 1/2 years of age, has not attained 18 years of age, has not completed a driver
2288 education course and has successfully passed all parts of an examination other than the
2299 driving test to apply for a learner's permit. A learner's permit issued to a person who is 15
3300 1/2 years of age under the bill requires a permittee to be accompanied by the permittee's
3311 parent or guardian or another responsible adult who is licensed to operate the class of
3322 vehicle operated by the permittee, has held a license for at least 2 years and is at least 25
3333 years of age. The accompanying operator must be seated beside the driver and is
3344 responsible for any violation of motor vehicle and traffic laws by the permittee. The bill
3355 also allows a person who is at least 18 years of age and who takes a driver education course
3366 that includes only classroom instruction through an adult education program to apply for
3377 or be issued a learner's permit upon successful completion of the course.
